description: The Department of Defense provides the military forces needed to deter war, and to protect the security of the United States.
name: Department of Defense

departments.description: This Requester Service Center (RSC) processes Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) requests for records related to the Office of the Secretary of Defense and Joint Staff (OSD/JS), to include the former U.S. Joint Forces Command (JFCOM), and other specific OSD components.* This RSC does not process FOIA requests for the entire Department of Defense (DoD). Please direct requests related to the Military Services, Combatant Commands, or other Defense Agencies, to the appropriate organization/component that maintains the record(s) of interest.

address_lines: OSD/JS FOIA Requester Service Center, Office of Freedom of Information

departments.name: Office of the Secretary and Joint Staff
departments.notes: This Office also handles requests for records of the U.S. Joint Forces Command, which was disestablished on August 31, 2011.

departments.name: Department of the Air Force
departments.description: The Air Force defends the United States in the air and space.

departments.name: Department of the Army
departments.description: Focusing on land operations, the U.S. Army organizes, trains, and equips active duty and Reserve forces to preserve the peace, security, and defense of the United States.
The Navy's primary mission is to defend the United States.

address_lines: FOIA Contact, Chief of Naval Operations

departments.name: Department of the Navy

departments.name: Armed Services Board of Contract Appeals
Defense Commissary Agency
departments.description: The Defense Commissary Agency provides a worldwide netowrk of commissaries that sell groceries and household supplies at low cost to members of the Armed Services.

The Defense Contract Audit Agency provides all contract audit services for the Department of Defense. This agency also provides accounting and financial advice to all Department of Defense components involved in procurement and contract administration.
departments.name: Defense Contract Audit Agency
Defense Contract Management Agency
departments.description: The Defense Contract Management Agency is responsible for contract management for the Department of Defense, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration, and several other federal, state, foreign and international goverments and agencies. Its goal is to ensure contracts are fulfilled on time and at the correct cost.

The Defense Finance and Accounting Service oversees payments to Department of Defense servicemembers, employees, vendors and contractors. The Defense Finance and Accounting Services also provides Department of Defense decision makers with business intelligence, finance and accounting information.
departments.name: Defense Finance and Accounting Service
departments.notes: This office has additional FOIA contact information that can be found by visiting its website.

departments.name: Defense Information Systems Agency

address_lines: ATTN:  Headquarters FOIA Requester Service Center

departments.description: The Defense Information Systems Agency provides a global infrastructure for information sharing and communication across the Department of Defense, from the President on down.
The Defense Intelligence Agency provides defense intelligence to "provide a decision advantage to warfighters, planners, and policy makers."
departments.name: Defense Intelligence Agency

departments.description: The Defense Logistics Agency provides logistical, acquisition, and technical support for the Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps and other federal agencies and allies.
departments.name: Defense Logistics Agency

departments.description: The Defense Security Service provides security for the Department of Defense and a number of other federal agencies. This includes providing industrial security oversight and assistance for contractor facilities.
departments.name: Defense Security Service
departments.notes: This office has additional FOIA contact information that can be found by visiting its website.

departments.description: The Defense Threat Reduction Agency is a combat support agency whose goal is to reduce the threat posed by weapons of mass destruction.
departments.name: Defense Threat Reduction Agency
Defense Technical Information Center
departments.description: The Defense Technical Information Center serves the Department of Defense as a repository of government funded scientific, technical, engineering and business related inormation.

departments.name: National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency
departments.description: The National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency provides location-based intelligence in support of national security.

departments.name: National Guard Bureau
departments.description: The National Guard assists in times of local emergency and can also be called into federal service.
The National Reconnaissance Office is responsible for designing, building, launching, and maintaining intelligence satellites.

National Security Agency

departments.description: The National Security Agency and Central Security Service are the "codemaker and codebreakers" of the intelligence community, providing foreign signal and communications intelligence to decision makers.

departments.description: Located between the European and Pacific combatant commands, U.S. Central Command’s area of responsibility covers the "central" area of the globe and consists of 20 countries — Afghanistan, Bahrain, Egypt, Iran, Iraq, Jordan, Kazakhstan, Kuwait, Kyrgyzstan, Lebanon, Oman, Pakistan, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Syria, Tajikistan, Turkmenistan, United Arab Emirates, Uzbekistan, and Yemen.
departments.name: U.S. Central Command
U.S. European Command
departments.description: The U.S. European Command works with partner nations to address regional issues, and keep the peace in Europe, parts of the Middle East, and Eurasia.

departments.name: U.S. Northern Command
departments.description: The Northern Command is responsible for defending the continental United States and Alaska, and for coordinating with the defenses of Canada, Mexico, and the Bahamas..

departments.name: U.S. Pacific Command

address_lines: ATTN: J151 FOIA Requester Service Center

departments.description: Headquartered in Hawaii, the U.S. Pacific Command is responsible for defending and promoting U.S. interests in the Pacific and Asia.

departments.name: U.S. Southern Command
departments.description: The U.S. Southern Command is responsible for security cooperation and operations in Central and South America and the Caribbean.

address_lines: HQ USSOCOM - SOCS-SJS-I/FOIA Requester Service Center

departments.name: U.S. Strategic Command
departments.description: U.S. Strategic Command is a unified command, incorporating elements of all military services, in an effort to detect and deter attacks against the U.S. and its allies. This mission includes nuclear deterrence, space, and cyberspace capabilities.

departments.name: U.S. Transportation Command
departments.description: The U.S. Transportation Command provides transportation services and capabilities to the other combatant commands, the military services and defense agencies..
